-- U.A.E. Will Spend $136 Billion on Airports, Al-Khaleej Reports
-- B y   T a m a r a   W a l i d
-- 2012-02-21T06:11:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-21/u-a-e-will-spend-136-billion-on-airports-al-khaleej-reports.html
The United Arab Emirates plans to
invest 500 billion dirhams ($136 billion) in aviation
infrastructure during the next 10 years and expects to get 15
million tourists by 2020,  Al-Khaleej  newspaper reported today,
citing Economy Minister Sultan al-Mansouri.  To contact the reporter on this story:
